Uses of Package
teal.field

  • Packages that use teal.field 
    Package Description
    teal.app
    This package rovides base classes and interfaces for the generic application SimPlayerApp and stand-alone applications.
    teal.field
    Provides general vector fields.
    teal.physics
    Physics properties and objects that may be added to the world.
    teal.physics.em
    Provides classes and interfaces for adding electromagnetic objects to the world.
    teal.sim.spatial
    Spatial objects do not have a physical 'body' but are used to represent field values and data visualizations.
    teal.visualization.dlic
    The top level IDraw package converted to use standard javax.vecmath and teal Field classes.
    teal.visualization.dlic.field
    Provides support classes for DLIC and DLICGenerator.
    teal.visualization.image
    Image processing and conversion classes.
  • Classes in teal.field used by teal.app 
    Class and Description
    Field
    A generic wrapper class for a Vector3dField which gets the potential of the field.
    Vector3dField
    Simple specification for any field of 3D double data, which is accessed through a location within the field.
  • Classes in teal.field used by teal.field 
    Class and Description
    CompositeField
    CompositeField represents the composite field generated by a series of objects.
    Field
    A generic wrapper class for a Vector3dField which gets the potential of the field.
    GenericFieldGenerator
    Provides methods for any generic field generator, which are envisioned as objects that have no physical representation, but generate "background" fields that add to the composite fields of the world.
    Vector3dField
    Simple specification for any field of 3D double data, which is accessed through a location within the field.
